<!-- Source from ejs templates -->
<%- include("../partials/header") %>

<!-- MAIN CONTENT HERE -->
<main>
  <h1>How did you... How did you do that?</h1>
  <h3><%= error ? error : "UNEXPECTED ERROR" %></h3>
  <p>We don't know how you created this error. Well done, you've outperformed our QA team! Unless this is Bob in QA, in
    which case, you're still behind the community on this one... Anyway, the steps you made to create this error
    have been logged with Bob, who will do everything in his power to see this page just like you did. Until he does,
    and figures out how to make it STOP sending you here, theres nothing left to do except:
  </p>
  <p><a href="javascript:history.back()">Go Back</a> or <a href="/">Return to the Homepage</a></p>
  <% if (NODE_ENV === 'development') { %>
  <details open>
    <summary>Error Details (Development Only)</summary>
    <pre><%= error %></pre>
    <pre><%= stack %></pre>
  </details>
  <% } %>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>